The Africa Continental Free Trade Agreement is arguably one of the most important continental economic developments to date.  This session explores ways in which the trade agreement dynamically shifts the economic paradigm in Africa from being a centre of extraction to potentially the worldâ€™s largest free trade area by 2050. Panellists will highlight the strategic role of the Africa Investment Forum to convene and leverage the collective capabilities of stakeholders to accelerate delivery of the objectives and aspirations of the agreement....